HEADWORD: Insitiency
<hw>In*si"ti*en*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + L. <ets>sitiens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>sitire</ets>
to be thirsty, fr. <ets>sitis</ets> thirst.]</ety> <def>Freedom from
thirst.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>insitiency</qex> of a camel for traveling in deserts.</q>
<rj><qau>Grew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insition</ent>⟦br⟧
